    <title>Water contributor: Christiana Z. Peppard</title>
    <description>Christiana Z. Peppard, Ph.D., is assistant professor of theology, science and ethics at Fordham University. Born in California’s Central Valley, her focus on water ethics is informed by the constraints of arid places and the fact that water is essential for all forms of survival. She is the author of Just Water: Theology, Ethics, and the Global Water Crisis. Find her on Twitter: @profpeppard.
</description>
